nhc_headline: ...NARDA QUICKLY WEAKENING... ...EXPECTED TO BECOME POST-TROPICAL THIS EVENING...
summary: ...NARDA QUICKLY WEAKENING... ...EXPECTED TO BECOME POST-TROPICAL THIS EVENING... As of 2:00 PM PDT Sun Sep 28 the center of Narda was located near 20.4, -125.4 with movement N at 8 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1008 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 40 mph.
